nic speeds in an English Electric Lighting and the Concorde.<ref name=\"38huffpost3\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Supersonic Flight Catastrophe in South Africa, One Year Later |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/supersonic-flights-fraugh_n_783346 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=6 December 2017}}</ref>\n* Weightlessness parabolic flights in an Ilyushin-76.<ref name=\"39popularmechanics\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=I Am Paying $200,000 for Five Minutes in Space |url=https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/rockets/a24264/virgin-galactic-astronaut/ |website=Popular Mechanics |accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref>\n* Flown in formation with the Breitling Jet Team.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Breitling Jet Team - What It's Really Like To Fly With The World's Wildest Pilots, The Breitling Jet Team |url=https://in.askmen.com/experience/1106498/article/breitling-jet-team |website=Ask Men |accessdate=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n* Aerobatic flight with [[Red Bull]] Race Team in [[Indianapolis]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Over, Under, Sideways, Down: Red Bull Air Race Ride-Along Thrills, Impresses |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/10/17/over-under-sideways-down-red-bull-air-races-thrill-impress/#269482ac64be |website=Forbes |accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>\n* Trained for upcoming [[Virgin Galactic]] flight in a centrifuge up to 6 Gs.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=The G Spot For Space Tourists |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2016/01/01/the-g-spot-for-space-tourists/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Autos===\n\nJim has driven several cars over 200 mph including:\n* A [[Bugatti]] Veyron at a top speed of 253.2 mph.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Bugatti Veyron\u2019s Top Speed \u2013 Strap In and Hunker Down |url=https://www.automobilemag.com/news/bugatti-veyrons-top-speed-james-clash/ |website=Automobile |accessdate=17 June 2009}}</ref>\n* Other 200-mph drives include Porsches, Ferraris, Lamborghinis, Bentleys, McLarens and Corvettes.<ref name=\"33forbes12\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Confessions Of A Speed Freak: Life At 200 MPH In Bugattis, Bentleys, Lamborghinis And Porsches |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2015/11/10/confessions-of-a-speed-freak-life-at-200-mph-in-bugattis-bentleys-lamborghinis-and-porsches/#61b78c7434fc |website=Forbes |accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref>\n* An IndyCar at an average lap speed of over 200 mph at Texas Motor Speedway.<ref name=\"34askmen3\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Driving 200 Mph In An Indy Car |url=https://www.askmen.com/entertainment/right-stuff/driving-200-mph-in-an-indycar.html |website=AskMen |accessdate=6 March 2019}}</ref>\n* Graduate of Frank Hawley Drag Racing School.<ref name=\"35forbes13\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Drive It Like You Stole It: Drag Racing Lessons Are Not For The Faint Of Heart |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/07/19/drive-it-like-you-stole-it-drag-racing-lessons-are-not-for-the-faint-of-heart/#1ab94f78220d |website=Forbes |accessdate=19 July 2017}}</ref>\n* Drove with [[Mario Andretti]] at 200 mph at Indianapolis Motor Speedway.<ref name=\"36forbes14\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Life in the Fastest Lane: Race Down the Indianapolis Motor Speedway at 200mph with Mario Andretti |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2016/07/06/racing-indianapolis-motor-speedway-mario-andretti/#44b9fc727e50 |website=Forbes |accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref>\n* Reported from start line while 11,000-hp nitro-methane dragsters blasted off to 330 mph in less than four seconds.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=NHRA Fans Love The Smell Of Nitro-Methane In The Morning |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2018/05/01/nhra-fans-love-the-smell-of-nitro-methane-in-the-morning/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=1 May 2018}}</ref>\n* Drove off-road Baja 1000 vehicles in Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Shaken, Not Stirred: Pounding Baja's Off-Road Desert Dust |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/07/27/shaken-not-stirred-pounding-bajas-off-road-desert-dust/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n* Drove a tank over a car.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Want To Crush Cars With A Tank? You Can Do It With This Minnesota Outfit |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/06/29/want-to-crush-a-car-with-a-60-ton-tank-a-minnesota-outfit-will-let-you-do-it-for-a-price/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=29 June 2017}}</ref>\n* Tested at Bonneville Salt Flats<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Blowing Salt at Bonneville |url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2005/0425/058.html |website=Forbes |accessdate=25 April 2005}}</ref>\n\n===Military===\n\n* Rode a B-52 bomber with The U.S. Air Force in Minot, [[North Dakota]].<ref name=\"46forbes18\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Ever Want To Fly An Old B-52 Bomber? Read This First-Person Account |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/10/02/ever-fly-in-an-old-b-52-bomber-as-a-civillian-read-this-first-person-acount/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=2 October 2017}}</ref>\n* Flew in a T-38 and suited up in a U-2 Space suit, Beale AFB, [[California]].<ref name=\"47forbes19\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Scuse Me While I Kiss The Sky: What It's Like To Fly In A Supersonic T-38 Talon |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2018/06/15/scuse-me-while-i-kiss-the-sky/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>\n* Embedded with U.S. Army 82nd Airborne, Fort Bragg, [[North Carolina]].<ref name=\"48forbes20\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Intrepid Reporter Embeds With Army's 82nd Airborne, Ft. Bragg |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2018/05/11/intrepid-reporter-embeds-with-armys-82nd-airborne-ft-bragg/#df4bfdc465ed |website=Forbes |accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n* Flew supersonic in an F-15 fighter jet at Seymour Johnson AFB, [[North Carolina]].<ref name=\"49forbes21\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=What's It Like To Go Supersonic In An F-15E Fighter Jet? Read On |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/08/17/what-is-it-like-to-go-supersonic-in-an-f-15e-fighter-jet-read-on/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=17 August 2017}}</ref>\n* Reported from nuclear missile bunker in Minot, [[North Dakota]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Visit A Live USAF Nuclear Missile Bunker 70 Feet Below Minot, ND |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2017/09/29/a-first-person-visit-to-a-nuclear-missile-silo-70-feet-below-minot-nd/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=29 September 2017}}</ref>\n* Reported from Thule AFB in northern [[Greenland]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=While You Sleep, Thule Listens, Watches, Waits |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2019/01/27/while-you-sleep-thule-listens-watches-waits/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=27 January 2017}}</ref>\n* Reported U.S. Air Force launch from Cape Canaveral, Florida<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Air Force/ULA Rocket Launch Provides Thrills, Chills But No Spills |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2019/03/18/air-forceula-rocket-launch-provides-thrills-chills-but-no-spills/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=18 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Mountains===\n\nSummited the following mountains:\n* [[Aconcagua]], [[Argentina]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* The [[Matterhorn]], [[Switzerland]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Mont Blanc]], [[France]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Kilimanjaro]], [[Tanzania]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Grand Teton]], [[Wyoming]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Orizaba]] and [[Popocateptl]], [[Mexico]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Cotapaxi]] and [[Cayambe (volcano)|Cayambe]], [[Ecuador]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* Virgin Peaks in [[Antarctica]] and [[Greenland]]<ref name=\"09theexplorersclub\" />\n* [[Mount Fuji]], [[Japan]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Sacred Mountain |url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2006/1127/074.html |website=Forbes |accessdate=17 November 2006}}</ref>\n* [[Kosciuszko]], [[Australia]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=The puny peak |url=https://www.forbes.com/global/1998/0810/0109080a.html |website=Forbes |accessdate=22 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===North and South Poles===\n\n* Skied the last degree (111km) to [[South Pole]].<ref name=\"41nbcnews\">{{cite web |title=South Pole Trek: SKiing to the Nth Degree |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/13481351/ns/travel-active_travel/t/south-pole-trek-skiing-nth-degree/ |website=NBC News |accessdate=25 July 2006}}</ref>\n* Reported from the [[North Pole]] and took the polar plunge.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Swimming with Santa |url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2000/1225/0326142a.html |website=Forbes |accessdate=22 March 2019}}</ref>\n* Visited high arctic outposts including [[Franz Josef Land]], [[Novaya Zemlya]], [[Wrangel Island]], [[Svalbard]], S'redny Island.<ref name=\"42startalk\">{{cite web |last1=Mullen |first1=Ian |title=Go to Extremes with Chuck Nice, Gary O'Reilly, Adventure Journalist Jim Clash and more |url=https://www.startalkradio.net/go-to-extremes-with-chuck-nice-gary-oreilly-adventure-journalist-jim-clash-and-more/ |website=Star Talk Radio |accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n===Oceans===\n\n* Participated in America\u2019s Cup Land Rover BAR race.<ref name=\"43forbes15\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Participatory Adventure: Sixth-Man Crew Duties Thrill At America's Cup NYC Race |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2016/05/08/participatory-adventure-sixth-man-crew-duties-thrill-at-americas-cup-nyc-race/#353bf08a1f77 |website=Forbes |accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n* Rode in Triton submersible to 1,000 feet below the Atlantic Ocean.<ref name=\"44forbes16\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Nekton Deep-Ocean Science: 1,000 Feet Below the Atlantic's Surface |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2016/07/30/nekton-deep-ocean-science-thrills-writer-1000-feet-below-atlantics-surface/#acdcdfc3cafb |website=Forbes |accessdate=7 July 2016}}</ref>\n* Drove a Superboat at 140 mph.<ref name=\"45forbes17\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Liquid Speed |url=https://www.forbes.com/2006/10/25/speed-boat-racing-forbeslife-sport-cz_jc_1027superboat.html|website=Forbes |accessdate=27 October 2006}}</ref>\n* Jet-skied with surfing champion [[Ken Bradshaw]] in 35-foot waves off Hawaii\u2019s North Shore.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=North Shore Surf Makes for Thrills and Spills in Hawaii |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/monster-north-shore-waves_n_5518779 |website=Huffpost |accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Other===\n\n* Stand-in bullfighter for PBR (Professional Bull Riders).<ref name=\"50pagesix\">{{cite web |last1=Mohr |first1=Ian |title=Explorers Club director to speak on bullfighting, Hemingway |url=https://pagesix.com/2014/04/16/explorers-club-director-to-speak-on-hemingway-space-travel/ |website=Page Six |accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref>\n* Bobsledded with the U.S. Olympic Team.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=James |title=Bobsleds Away! |url=https://www.forbes.com/free_forbes/2007/0903/149.html |website=Forbes |accessdate=3 September 2007}}</ref>\n* Tested bullet-proof jacket getting shot point blank with a .38 caliber.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=Bulletproof Clothing |url=https://me.askmen.com/apparel/1089069/article/bulletproof-clothing |website=Ask Men |accessdate=22 March 2019}}</ref>\n* Highest, longest rappel in the world at 367 feet.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=South Africa's 367-Foot Record Rappel Provides Big Adrenaline Jolt, Views |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2014/12/22/south-africas-367-foot-record-rappel-provides-big-adrenaline-jolt-views/#38f1493440e9 |website=Forbes |accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref>\n* Figure-skated with Olympic Silver Medalist Sasha Cohen.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gladden |first1=Becca |title=Jim Clash - Business and Adventure Journalist, Author - Part One |url=https://www.inspiring-figures.com/single-post/2018/03/28/Jim-Clash-%E2%80%93-Business-and-Adventure-Journalist-Author-%E2%80%93-Part-One |website=Inspiring Figures |accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"51forbes22\">{{cite web |last1=Clash |first1=Jim |title=South Africa's 367-Foot Record Rappel Provides Big Adrenaline Jolt, Views |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/2014/12/22/south-africas-367-foot-record-rappel-provides-big-adrenaline-jolt-views/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=22 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.forbes.com/sites/jimclash/ Contributor Page on Forbes]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clash, Jim}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:American male journalists]]\n[[Category:Journalists from New York City]]\n[[Category:Writers from New York City]]\n[[Category:Sportswriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Explorers Club]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control, addedorphantag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Clash"}
